    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-03T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-03T11:00:00-05:00" n="147"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/802: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heath</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-03T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 3, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1644. My 1641, June 3, 4 p.m.<note n="83" xml:id="d147fn83">Not printed.</note> I
                    was requested to call at the Foreign Office this morning by Ritter who stated
                    that prompt orders had been issued to the German naval units to prevent any
                    molestations of the S. S. <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi> and in amplification
                    of his remarks handed me a copy of the press communiqué transmitted in my
                    telegram under reference. He said that while he could not guarantee the <hi
                        rend="italic">bona fides</hi> of the story of a Franco-British plot to sink
                    the <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi> as well as other American vessels the
                    information had been received from what the Foreign Office regarded as
                    trustworthy sources. He further asserted that according to German information
                    the alleged plot involved both the use of a time-bomb within the ship and a
                    torpedo attack from outside.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
